spec: mp3256
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.managers.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 664 (mp3256): __rpow__, __rlshift__, __rrshift__ dict-presence (reflected power/shift) for multiprocessing types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: multiprocessing.Process, pool.Pool, pool.AsyncResult, pool.MapResult, managers.SyncManager, managers.BaseListProxy, managers._BaseDictProxy, managers._BaseSetProxy."
    - "Key finding (__rpow__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rpow__. multiprocessing.Process manages a subprocess lifecycle (start/join/terminate/kill); reflected power is undefined for process objects. pool.Pool dispatches work to worker processes; n ** pool is not a defined Python expression. pool.AsyncResult and pool.MapResult are result handles; reflected power is absent. managers.BaseListProxy proxies list — list does NOT define __rpow__ (list has no power data model from either side). managers._BaseDictProxy proxies dict — dict defines neither __pow__ nor __rpow__. managers._BaseSetProxy proxies set — set does not support power of any kind. managers.SyncManager: server process hosting shared objects; no power protocol defined."
    - "Key finding (__rlshift__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rlshift__. Reflected left shift is the mirror of __lshift__. multiprocessing types define no __lshift__ (confirmed false in wave 660), so __rlshift__ is also absent. Process/Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult are process-management and result-handle types. managers.BaseListProxy proxies list — list defines no __lshift__ or __rlshift__. managers._BaseDictProxy proxies dict — dict defines no shift operators. managers._BaseSetProxy proxies set — set defines no left shift from either side. managers.SyncManager: no shift protocol defined."
    - "Key finding (__rrshift__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rrshift__. Reflected right shift (__rrshift__) is invoked when n >> obj is attempted. multiprocessing types define no __rshift__ (confirmed false in wave 660), so __rrshift__ is equally absent. Critical note on managers.BaseListProxy and managers._BaseDictProxy: neither list nor dict defines __rrshift__. managers._BaseSetProxy proxies set — set defines no right shift operator from either side. managers.SyncManager, Process, Pool, AsyncResult, MapResult: none implement a right-shift or streaming interface. None of the 8 subjects expose the >> operator from either side."
    - "Proxy class note — BaseListProxy: wave 658 found BaseListProxy.__add__ = true and BaseListProxy.__mul__ = true (forwarding list's + and * operators). Waves 662–663 confirmed all reflected arithmetic and division/modulo operators are false for BaseListProxy. This wave confirms BaseListProxy.__rpow__ = false, __rlshift__ = false, __rrshift__ = false (list has none of these reflected power or shift operators)."
    - "All 24 values in this wave are false. multiprocessing is a process-based concurrency library; its entire API is expressed through explicit method calls, subprocess lifecycle management, and IPC — never through Python's reflected power or shift operators."
    - "Cross-wave summary for mp subjects:"
    - "  Wave 658 (mp3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — BaseListProxy __add__=true, __mul__=true; others false."
    - "  Wave 659 (mp3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 660 (mp3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 661 (mp3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 662 (mp3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 663 (mp3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 664 (mp3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 8."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __rpow__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__rpow__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rpow__.
# Process/Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: process-management and result-handle
#   types; reflected power is not defined for any of them.
# managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — list does NOT define __rpow__.
#   Python's list has no power data model from either side; n ** list
#   triggers int's __pow__ which rejects list, and list has no __rpow__
#   fallback. Therefore BaseListProxy has no __rpow__.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict — dict defines no __pow__ or
#   __rpow__.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set — set does not support power
#   from either side.
# managers.SyncManager: server process; no arithmetic protocol defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table mp3256.rpow:
  description: "multiprocessing types __rpow__ dict-presence checks; wave 664"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
  id_prefix: mp3256

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - ["mp3256001", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.Process.__dict__,                 "__rpow__"], false]
    - ["mp3256002", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__dict__,               "__rpow__"], false]
    - ["mp3256003", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.AsyncResult.__dict__,        "__rpow__"], false]
    - ["mp3256004", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.MapResult.__dict__,          "__rpow__"], false]
    - ["mp3256005", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__dict__,    "__rpow__"], false]
    - ["mp3256006", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.BaseListProxy.__dict__,  "__rpow__"], false]
    - ["mp3256007", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseDictProxy.__dict__, "__rpow__"], false]
    - ["mp3256008", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy.__dict__,  "__rpow__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __rlshift__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__rlshift__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rlshift__.
# Process/Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: process-management types
#   with no bitwise or shift semantics of any kind.
# managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — list defines no __lshift__ or
#   __rlshift__. n << list is not a valid Python expression.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict — dict defines no shift operators.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set — set defines no left shift from
#   either side. The proxy's _method IPC callthrough handles no shift ops.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table mp3256.rlshift:
  description: "multiprocessing types __rlshift__ dict-presence checks; wave 664"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
  id_prefix: mp3256

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - ["mp3256009",  operator.contains, [multiprocessing.Process.__dict__,                 "__rlshift__"], false]
    - ["mp3256010",  operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__dict__,               "__rlshift__"], false]
    - ["mp3256011",  operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.AsyncResult.__dict__,        "__rlshift__"], false]
    - ["mp3256012",  operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.MapResult.__dict__,          "__rlshift__"], false]
    - ["mp3256013",  operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__dict__,    "__rlshift__"], false]
    - ["mp3256014",  operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.BaseListProxy.__dict__,  "__rlshift__"], false]
    - ["mp3256015",  operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseDictProxy.__dict__, "__rlshift__"], false]
    - ["mp3256016",  operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy.__dict__,  "__rlshift__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __rrshift__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__rrshift__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rrshift__.
# Process/Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: process-management types;
#   reflected right shift is not defined.
# managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — list does NOT define __rrshift__.
#   list has no shift semantics from either side.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict — dict defines no __rrshift__.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set — set defines no right shift operator
#   from either side; sets are not bitwise-shift types.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

